## CHARACTER MOMENT WISHLIST

### Ahdia
- Processing first kill guilt (Firas's death in Book 1)
- Living months in utopia timeline, then erasing it
- Falling in love with AR-Ryu
- Falling in love with real-Ryu
- Losing both when time traveling
- Choosing to let Geneva/Bellatrix die
- Carrying knowledge of alternate timeline alone
- Losing her powers completely
- Learning parkour on Firas's routes (grief)
- "I'm just... Ahdia" (without powers, who am I?)
- Training WITH team, not above them
- First time actually hurt in fight (powerless)
- Identity crisis: Fragment of Bellatrix AND fully herself
- "I'm enough as I am" moment (Book 7)
- Accepting she can't save everyone
- Grief for unchosen timelines
- Could visit timeline where Firas lived, chooses not to
- Could prevent Montana trauma, chooses not to (acceptance)
- Final confrontation with Bellatrix: "You tried doing everything. I learned being everything."

### Bellatrix/Naima
- Hundreds of iterations reveal
- Tried being the VILLAIN - failed
- Tried being the HERO (Geneva) - failed
- Tried being absent - failed
- Tried being involved - failed
- Even achieved perfection (utopia) - failed
- Consciousness copy horror
- "I made you to understand me" conversation
- Revealing herself to Ahdia as Geneva during catastrophe
- "I've tried this path before. I know what comes next."
- "Even perfection didn't work. The problem is you existing."
- Final confrontation dialogue (Story Bible)
- Tragic villain, not pure evil
- Genuine love for what she created
- Ultimate loneliness despite infinite attempts
- Can't accept that some problems have no solutions

### The Intermediary
- Learning human customs (awkward interactions)
